INTRUSION DETECTION SYSTEM (IDS): IDS is a software system or hardware device that inspects all inbound network traffic for suspicious patterns that may indiacate a network or system security breach.

--->IDS also reffered as a packet sniffer.
---> signature comparison

TYPES:
1.Network based IDS
2.Host based IDS

FIREWALL:
firewalls are hardware/software designed to prevent unauthorized access to or from a private network.

HONEYPOT: a honeypot is a computer system on the internet intended to attract and trap those who attempt unauthorized actions.

